{
  "text": "Our current data demonstrate that levels of CAR and integrin \u03b1 v \u03b2 3 expression are high in DU145 and low in PC3 cells, which is similar to the findings in a previous study by Adams et. al. [CITATION_1] . Interestingly, our current study found that integrin \u03b1 v \u03b2 5 expression was high in DU145 and PC3 cells. This is inconsistent with Adams' study [CITATION_2] , which showed that integrin \u03b1 v \u03b2 5 expression is high in DU145, but low in PC3 cells. However, consistent with our results, levels of integrin \u03b1 v \u03b2 5 were higher than integrin \u03b1 v \u03b2 3 in PC3 cells in Adams' report. [CITATION_3] . However, the amounts of integrin \u03b1 v \u03b2 5 varied. Another previous study [CITATION_4] also demonstrated that PC3 and LNCaP cells expressed integrin \u03b1 v \u03b2 5 at similar levels, which is consistent with our current results. Thus, further study is needed to verify these data and their underlying molecular mechanisms.",
  "correct_citation": {
